JO  - AMJ
SP  - 957
EP  - 971
VL  - 37
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We investigated differences in the costs and benefits associated with being a mentor in a matched sample of 80 male and BO female executives. Women were as likely as men to be mentors and reported outcomes and intentions for future mentoring similar to men's. Implications and areas for future research are discussed.
AB  - We investigated differences in the costs and benefits associated with being a mentor in a matched sample of 80 male and BO female executives. Women were as likely as men to be mentors and reported outcomes and intentions for future mentoring similar to men's. Implications and areas for future research are discussed.
